# UI Design Standards - chadcn/ui New York Style

## Design System Guidelines

- **Primary Framework**: Use chadcn/ui components with the "New York" style variant
- **Style Configuration**: Ensure `components.json` is set to `"style": "new-york"`
- **Base Color Palette**: Use neutral base colors for consistency
- **CSS Variables**: Leverage CSS custom properties for theming flexibility
- **Component Library**: Prioritize chadcn/ui components before creating custom ones

## Visual Design Principles

### Component Aesthetics
- **Modern & Clean**: Embrace the contemporary aesthetic of the New York style
- **Subtle Shadows**: Apply delicate shadow effects to buttons, inputs, selects, and date pickers
- **Compact Sizing**: Use smaller, more refined component dimensions
- **Refined Borders**: Implement distinctive border radii that align with the New York style
- **Focused States**: Use consistent focus state implementations across all interactive elements

### Layout & Spacing
- **Consistent Spacing**: Follow Tailwind CSS spacing scale for consistent margins and padding
- **Grid Systems**: Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for responsive layouts
- **Typography Scale**: Maintain visual hierarchy with consistent font sizes and weights
- **White Space**: Use generous white space to create breathing room and improve readability

## Component Standards

### Button Components
- Use chadcn/ui Button component with New York styling
- Apply appropriate variants: default, destructive, outline, secondary, ghost, link
- Ensure proper sizing: default, sm, lg, icon
- Include subtle shadow effects as per New York style

### Form Elements
- Implement Input, Select, Checkbox, and other form components with New York styling
- Maintain consistent border treatments and focus states
- Use proper validation states and error messaging
- Apply compact sizing for better space utilization

### Navigation & Layout
- Use Card components for content grouping with appropriate shadows
- Implement Dialog/Modal components following New York conventions
- Apply consistent separator and divider styling
- Use ScrollArea for contained scrollable content

## Implementation Standards

### Component Usage
- **Prefer chadcn/ui**: Always use chadcn/ui components when available
- **Consistent Imports**: Use proper component imports from the established alias structure
- **Variant Selection**: Choose appropriate component variants that align with New York style
- **Customization**: Only customize components when necessary, maintaining style consistency

### Styling Approach
- **Tailwind-First**: Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- **CSS Variables**: Leverage the established CSS custom property system
- **Theme Integration**: Ensure all components respect light/dark mode switching
- **Responsive Design**: Implement mobile-first responsive design patterns

### Color System
- **Neutral Base**: Use the neutral color palette as the foundation
- **Semantic Colors**: Apply semantic colors (success, warning, error) consistently
- **Accessibility**: Ensure proper contrast ratios for WCAG compliance
- **Brand Integration**: Incorporate brand colors while maintaining New York style integrity

## File Organization

### Component Structure
- Store UI components in `src/components/ui/` following chadcn/ui conventions
- Place custom components in `src/components/` with clear naming
- Group related components in logical subdirectories
- Maintain separate files for complex component variants

### Style Management
- Central theming through `src/index.css` with CSS variables
- Component-specific styles should extend the base New York theme
- Avoid inline styles; prefer Tailwind classes or styled components
- Document custom styling decisions for team consistency

## Best Practices

### Development Workflow
- **Design Tokens**: Use established design tokens for spacing, colors, and typography
- **Component Library**: Build a cohesive component library following New York patterns
- **Documentation**: Document component usage and styling decisions
- **Testing**: Ensure components work across different screen sizes and themes

### Maintenance
- **Consistency Audits**: Regularly review components for New York style compliance
- **Updates**: Stay current with chadcn/ui updates while maintaining local customizations
- **Performance**: Optimize component bundle size and rendering performance
- **Accessibility**: Maintain ARIA compliance and keyboard navigation support

